WEBVTT

00:00.866 --> 00:05.252
Today, our New Testament reading comes from Philippians 4.

00:05.432 --> 00:06.994
It's a very familiar passage.

00:07.014 --> 00:11.540
We begin in the fourth verse and read through the seventh verse.

00:14.504 --> 00:16.167
Rejoice in the Lord always.

00:17.088 --> 00:19.111
And again, I say rejoice.

00:20.653 --> 00:22.215
Let everyone see your gentleness.

00:23.116 --> 00:24.318
The Lord is near.

00:24.778 --> 00:26.521
Do not be anxious about anything.

00:27.302 --> 00:30.386
Instead, in every situation,

00:31.298 --> 00:37.627
through prayer and petition with thanksgiving, tell your quest to God.

00:38.749 --> 00:49.244
And the peace of God that surpasses all understanding will guard your hearts and minds in Christ Jesus.

00:50.065 --> 00:52.869
This is the word of God for the people of God.

00:55.713 --> 00:59.058
Over the last several weeks, Andy and I have

01:00.226 --> 01:04.630
and Mary Beth have been preaching on the idea of salt and light.

01:05.791 --> 01:15.320
The fact that as a Christian, we should be affected by God's love and affect the world by our love.

01:15.921 --> 01:30.034
And we've tried to talk about the things that enable us to be the salt and light that keep us from losing our brightness and our joy and losing our savoriness and the way we season and flavor the world.

01:30.146 --> 01:30.687
for God.

01:32.389 --> 01:43.865
Today, I think what we're talking about is one of the most incredible mysteries and unused gifts that we have in the Christian faith.

01:44.926 --> 01:46.208
And that's the gift of prayer.

01:47.450 --> 01:56.562
So many times, as you heard in the children's sermon, we're so worried that we can't pray as long a prayer as the preacher.

01:56.898 --> 02:00.164
are as eloquent a prayers as the preacher.

02:00.225 --> 02:05.214
And so we're kind of guarded in the way we go about praying.

02:06.136 --> 02:09.242
Let me ask you, what was the first prayer you ever learned?

02:11.347 --> 02:13.611
Now I lay me down to sleep.

02:13.651 --> 02:16.357
How many of you can recite that from memory still?

02:17.178 --> 02:19.122
What was another prayer you learned early?

02:20.514 --> 02:25.138
God is great, God is good, let us thank Him for our food.

02:25.219 --> 02:28.101
We pray about the important things, sleep and food.

02:28.922 --> 02:33.286
We're gonna have God cover those and take care of those.

02:33.506 --> 02:41.434
But the other way we learn is situationally in life, we find ourselves in circumstances where we are overwhelmed.

02:41.514 --> 02:49.682
I think about the story my brother-in-law used to tell, and those of you who've been here while I was here have heard me tell us, my brother-in-law Wayne was having a wedding,

02:49.826 --> 02:53.514
And this is like a universal thing that happens.

02:53.574 --> 02:58.344
In the middle of the wedding, there was one particular child that was over enjoying themselves.

02:59.987 --> 03:02.532
And they were drawing tension to themselves.

03:03.114 --> 03:09.106
And at the same time, the universal is there was a parent there that would have killed them on site if it was legal.

03:09.346 --> 03:10.447
and drug them out the way.

03:10.507 --> 03:13.191
But what happens is, is this what happens with most parents?

03:13.651 --> 03:18.157
The parents snatched that child up, threw them on their shoulder and headed for the back door.

03:18.458 --> 03:23.584
And as they were walking to the back door, the kid just leaned out and said, y'all pray for me.

03:23.644 --> 03:32.876
Sometimes we come into circumstances that we just feel overwhelmed and we need some help, sweet Jesus.

03:33.337 --> 03:34.418
Help us please.

03:37.250 --> 03:53.107
As much as we laugh and as much as we pray, every Sunday we pray the Lord's prayer, what I've found in my life is I still hadn't captured the full benefit that God offers me in the gift of prayer.

03:56.891 --> 04:01.937
In this season of the year, in our family, we have kind of a special season.

04:01.957 --> 04:05.681
You got valentines coming up on February 15th.

04:05.781 --> 04:06.802
I met Cindy.

04:07.138 --> 04:15.826
But on February 10th, here, 2006, I had quadruple bypass surgery.

04:18.229 --> 04:21.412
And I got to come home on Valentine's.

04:23.434 --> 04:33.143
But during the surgery and afterwards, I made an incidental discovery about the nature of prayer.

04:33.343 --> 04:35.986
Have you ever learned something about backing into it?

04:38.626 --> 04:47.600
While I was having my surgery and when I went into recovery, Cindy was waiting for him to get word and she never got word and she never got word and she never got word.

04:48.481 --> 04:53.769
And finally, they went up and told her that I'd had some issues.

04:53.809 --> 04:54.831
The issues were this.

04:55.131 --> 05:00.780
When I woke up in the recovery room, it was really dark and I was by myself and I was hurting like crazy.

05:00.800 --> 05:02.322
My back was aching.

05:02.562 --> 05:04.224
And it was dark.

05:04.304 --> 05:10.292
I didn't think there was anybody in there, and I just said, oh, and I heard a nurse say, oh, so you're awake.

05:11.854 --> 05:14.637
And I'm like, yeah, my back is killing me.

05:15.258 --> 05:16.459
And she said, well, it should.

05:16.519 --> 05:18.942
You had a fight with the orderlies.

05:18.983 --> 05:22.247
You pulled your intubation too bad, and we don't like you very much.

05:28.074 --> 05:31.378
You see, when I was young, I'd nearly drowned, and I have this

05:31.586 --> 05:34.131
claustrophobic feeling of not being able to breathe.

05:34.191 --> 05:40.723
And so every time I get intubated, every when I got my CPAP, I just have this sense of, I gotta breathe, I gotta breathe.

05:41.023 --> 05:49.579
When I went home, I would wake up and scare Cindy to death at night because I would have epic episodes of not being able to breathe.

05:51.563 --> 05:53.426
And as I laid there and healed,

05:53.570 --> 05:57.455
and was mad at God for being sick and mad at God for not being able to preach.

05:57.795 --> 06:03.623
I was trying to pray and all of a sudden I realized spiritually I was having that same feeling.

06:06.647 --> 06:08.369
I couldn't catch my spiritual breath.

06:11.012 --> 06:12.594
I felt like I was suffocating.

06:14.717 --> 06:16.579
I felt like I was dying.

06:19.303 --> 06:21.906
Have you ever been in a hold your breath contest?

06:24.226 --> 06:25.508
I don't know, maybe that's something a young boy.

06:25.728 --> 06:32.076
Whenever we were staying in Oklahoma City, my brother and I would go to the pool and see who could swim under the water longest.

06:32.457 --> 06:34.720
And I'm a very determined, stubborn person.

06:34.740 --> 06:37.684
I would have died underwater before I let him beat me.

06:38.585 --> 06:44.933
And so there would be, but there would be times when I would come out of the water and just think, you know, I don't know if I'm going to make it.

06:48.638 --> 06:51.602
The gift of prayer from God.

06:53.314 --> 06:59.341
I'm beginning to discover for me to capture it is much like the gift of breath.

07:02.084 --> 07:08.191
It is this beautiful in and out that brings life.

07:10.194 --> 07:20.946
Part of the reason I'm on a CPAP machine is because not just that I snore, but because when I do sleep, I don't breathe in enough oxygen.

07:22.050 --> 07:24.533
to properly allow me to sleep well.

07:25.674 --> 07:43.732
And so that little machine pumps that air into my lungs and oxygenates my blood and allows it to circulate through my body in order for me to exhale that carbon dioxide and begin again.

07:43.752 --> 07:49.458
When Jesus said to us, pray without ceasing,

07:50.978 --> 07:54.623
What he meant was pray like your breathing.

07:57.488 --> 08:01.794
It not only is a rhythm, it is the gift of life.

08:03.577 --> 08:06.601
It is drawing upon the very presence of God.

08:06.962 --> 08:15.474
It is reclaiming the gift that God gave us in creation of walking and talking with them every single moment of life.

08:15.906 --> 08:25.138
and that we cast away every time we turn from Him and don't breathe in His presence.

08:25.158 --> 08:38.095
If you watch the rhythm of Jesus' life, He prayed in every situation from the temptation to the garden to the cross.

08:40.878 --> 08:43.602
Every conversation He had with people

08:43.810 --> 08:46.534
was laced with a conversation with God.

08:48.938 --> 08:57.171
It was as natural for him as breathing in and breathing out.

08:58.954 --> 09:05.243
Paul wrote to the church at Ephesus, that early church that you should rejoice in the Lord always.

09:05.343 --> 09:07.026
And again, I say rejoice.

09:07.746 --> 09:10.329
But then he turns around and says, but I know you're anxious.

09:10.409 --> 09:12.251
Don't be anxious about anything.

09:12.651 --> 09:20.339
But with prayer and supplication, allow God to give you the gift of peace.

09:21.641 --> 09:27.247
How many times are you sitting there during the day and you think, well, I just breathe eight times in that minute.

09:29.289 --> 09:30.290
Do you ever think about that?

09:30.330 --> 09:33.674
No, because the breathing comes.

09:33.894 --> 09:37.618
How many times when you have a cold or sinus, do you think,

09:37.698 --> 09:38.980
I can't breathe.

09:41.204 --> 09:41.484
Yeah.

09:43.728 --> 09:52.904
In our faith, the rhythm of our faith is directly tied to our ability to be in prayer with God.

09:54.526 --> 09:56.750
I love as I was, I was prepared for this.

09:56.830 --> 10:00.657
To be honest, I told Cindy this and those of you who are preachers will understand what I'm saying.

10:00.997 --> 10:03.922
I had a really good sermon prepared Friday.

10:05.570 --> 10:10.495
And when I got up this morning, God wasn't happy with it, so we changed.

10:13.579 --> 10:18.905
And what it reminded me of was this breathe in, breathe out.

10:20.567 --> 10:30.337
The fact that God is with us in real time, that He knows when we need His help as we're being toted down the church and about to be walked.

10:33.180 --> 10:34.642
He knows when we haven't

10:35.522 --> 10:39.087
been caught up in breathing him in and having enough air.

10:40.869 --> 10:45.415
And so as I walked around in that this morning, I began to think about the rhythm of the Lord's prayer.

10:47.378 --> 10:57.712
And it is this beautiful example of how we should pray our Father who art in heaven, hallowed be thy name.

10:58.072 --> 11:01.497
Thy kingdom come, thy will be done on earth as it is in heaven.

11:03.299 --> 11:05.522
Breathing in the goodness of God.

11:05.858 --> 11:07.740
Breathing in the power of God.

11:07.780 --> 11:10.063
Breathing in the Word of God.

11:10.184 --> 11:12.406
Breathing in the will of God.

11:15.190 --> 11:18.815
And we bring in that oxygen and that life giving force.

11:21.538 --> 11:25.283
But then what do we follow that prayer with?

11:26.084 --> 11:30.610
Give us this day our daily bread.

11:31.714 --> 11:38.524
and forgive us our trespasses as we forgive those who trespass against us, and lead us not to temptation.

11:42.950 --> 11:53.746
We exhale that carbon-to-not dioxide, those things in our life, our sins, our stresses, those things that weigh upon our heart, those concerns that are

11:53.826 --> 11:58.751
crippling us and making us anxious and afraid those things that are taking our peace.

11:59.211 --> 12:12.384
And as we exhale them, everything from God, I don't know how I'm going to pay the bills at the end of the month to dear Lord, in this social media world, it's all I can do to keep my civility.

12:14.225 --> 12:19.791
We're breathing out that which is contaminating our body unless we get it out.

12:22.753 --> 12:23.474
But then

12:25.090 --> 12:31.720
We breathe in for thine is the kingdom and the power and the glory forever.

12:36.027 --> 12:37.289
That's why Paul can write.

12:39.112 --> 12:40.834
Don't be anxious about anything.

12:40.854 --> 12:45.842
Breathe in the goodness of God.

12:48.098 --> 12:55.225
Breathe out the things that weigh you down, the things that contaminate your life, the sins, the brokenness.

12:55.745 --> 13:12.582
And the miraculous, wonderful genius of God's creation is while each of us is walking around breathing in and out of our lives, He is putting us together to make sure that we're all breathing.

13:15.324 --> 13:16.946
Have you ever had to give CPR?

13:20.738 --> 13:21.619
Some of you are not.

13:25.304 --> 13:30.270
As the community of faith, it's our job to make sure everybody's breathing.

13:32.733 --> 13:39.902
To make sure everybody is somehow in that rhythm of, God is good, I am broken.

13:41.164 --> 13:43.106
God is good, I'm afraid.

13:46.310 --> 13:49.554
And the incredible third dimension of prayer

13:49.762 --> 14:06.465
is not just the breathing in of oxygen and the exhaling of the carbon dioxide and the things that break us, but it is the fact that actually that action brings us life and then we become salt and light for each other because we're alive.

14:10.510 --> 14:19.442
In my heart journey, another little episode when we were in Hattiesburg, I woke up one night, couldn't get peace, called my doctor, couldn't get my doctor,

14:19.554 --> 14:25.283
call my cardiologist, couldn't give my cardiologist, woke Cindy up and said, I'm not right, I need to go the doctor.

14:28.147 --> 14:29.570
Finally, the doctors call back.

14:29.610 --> 14:34.277
They met me at the hospital as they were getting me out of the vehicle.

14:36.340 --> 14:38.884
I just heard the nurses say, we're losing him.

14:38.904 --> 14:41.629
His blood pressure is 68 over 40.

14:42.209 --> 14:46.055
He's thrown a blood clot to his heart.

14:46.075 --> 14:47.698
They gave me the clot buster.

14:48.002 --> 14:59.221
And all I can remember is just nothing until I was awake again.

15:02.847 --> 15:04.029
And I was breathing again.

15:04.069 --> 15:07.775
And my heart was beaten again.

15:10.459 --> 15:14.546
You see, our prayer life is directly connected to our heart life.

15:16.866 --> 15:26.759
to not have the Spirit of God in us, to not have the life of God in us means our heart can't do its business.

15:28.481 --> 15:39.015
I know way more than I want to know about my circulatory system, but this I know the heart takes good stuff in and pumps good stuff out to the lungs.

15:41.719 --> 15:43.922
And that just as in our faith,

15:44.066 --> 15:45.909
We want to have good hearts.

15:46.029 --> 15:57.306
We can't have it without a life of prayer, without a life of the conversation with God to hear his voice.

15:57.326 --> 16:00.050
How many of you've heard God speak directly to you?

16:02.594 --> 16:03.816
Has it been very office?

16:03.876 --> 16:05.198
That's kind of a Moses thing.

16:05.459 --> 16:10.386
When God talks to you, you're even big trouble or you got big stuff ahead of you.

16:13.538 --> 16:16.381
But I've heard Jesus speak to me in the scripture.

16:18.824 --> 16:21.848
I've heard the Holy Spirit speak to me in my soul.

16:25.231 --> 16:30.117
You see, the cool thing about that breathing in is there's no language required.

16:32.740 --> 16:33.801
The Bible says it.

16:36.064 --> 16:41.490
God understands our grunts, our moans, our wordless moments.

16:42.562 --> 16:44.786
And that's the other side of prayer.

16:46.148 --> 16:52.840
We don't have a God who sits up there and twittles thumbs and waits for crisis.

16:55.064 --> 16:56.747
God is still in the garden.

17:00.474 --> 17:02.958
He's walking with you whether you're talking to him or not.

17:04.661 --> 17:07.346
He's talking with you whether you're listening or not.

17:08.546 --> 17:19.403
He's leading you, guiding you, comforting you, sending what you need, whether you are paying attention or not, God is all in on you.

17:21.286 --> 17:31.802
He was all in in creation and He will be all in until He recreates and Jesus comes home and we're living in the revelation truth of a new creation.

17:35.528 --> 17:37.010
And the invitation is simple.

17:39.938 --> 17:40.579
Breathe.

17:43.903 --> 17:56.441
You want to know why so many people who are about yoga and meditation and spiritual things focus so much on your breathing.

17:58.884 --> 17:59.805
Breathe deeply.

18:02.349 --> 18:05.413
Let it go all the way to your toes before you exhale.

18:08.137 --> 18:08.978
When I was in

18:09.154 --> 18:15.322
junior college, this will date me, I took a speed reading course.

18:15.342 --> 18:17.044
Any of y'all ever taking a speed reading course?

18:19.887 --> 18:21.169
It's a blessing and a curse.

18:23.251 --> 18:27.016
I'm married to a woman who will read every single word in every single book.

18:27.156 --> 18:29.519
She is not going to speed read anything.

18:30.640 --> 18:36.467
And it frustrates the tarnation out of her when I'm reading a chapter in about 10 minutes.

18:36.507 --> 18:38.770
He's like, did you even know what that says?

18:40.770 --> 18:43.513
A lot of us try to live our spirituality like that.

18:43.533 --> 18:49.399
We hyperventilize like, breathe out, breathe out, breathe in, breathe out, breathe in, breathe out, breathe in, breathe out.

18:49.439 --> 18:49.980
You know what happens?

18:50.000 --> 18:50.701
You pass out.

18:53.304 --> 18:54.505
You lose consciousness.

18:54.905 --> 18:57.709
That's not how we were designed to pray.

18:58.129 --> 19:10.002
It's not praying curses on people who cut you off in the traffic or asking for blessings when you're waiting on the numbers for the lottery.

19:11.234 --> 19:13.396
Oh, you'd laugh too much on that.

19:15.979 --> 19:28.994
It is more that deep inhaling life, letting life feel your body, and then taking the opportunity to exhale the other things.

19:29.014 --> 19:31.077
We're about to end the season of Lent.

19:31.097 --> 19:39.026
In the New Testament, the word for prayer, really, if you look at the Hebrew word and the Aramaic word, they don't exactly match up.

19:41.154 --> 19:53.510
The Hebrew word is the sense of bringing yourself and your needs and your sins to God.

19:55.112 --> 19:57.816
It is that exhale.

19:59.118 --> 20:08.370
Their make word is more centered in finding yourself in the presence and dialogue with God.

20:10.562 --> 20:31.470
There's this beautiful tension that we live in that calls us not only to celebrate the goodness that God can be and bring in our life, but it also means if you don't breathe out, if you don't get those toxic things out of you, you're going to die.

20:31.810 --> 20:37.458
How many of you have heard the number of people who have died during this cold spell of carbon monoxide poisoning?

20:41.858 --> 20:44.101
If you're inhaling the wrong things, you're gonna die.

20:46.264 --> 20:51.151
If you're seeking to breathe in things that are not of life, you're gonna die.

20:52.953 --> 20:54.715
Perfect chemical example.

20:55.837 --> 21:01.364
If you breathe in oxygen, you talk and act and live normally, you ever breathe in helium?

21:02.987 --> 21:05.270
Oh my, what's gonna happen to you?

21:05.290 --> 21:11.378
You breathe it in and you talk funny because it's not what your body's made to do, so it causes you to

21:11.874 --> 21:12.795
be a little weird.

21:15.277 --> 21:27.290
If you breathe in the wrong things, it causes you to be a little weird and maybe a little sick and maybe even eventually a little dead.

21:30.153 --> 21:35.378
Jesus said, I've come that you might have life and have it abundantly.

21:37.100 --> 21:39.442
He loves you that much.

21:41.986 --> 21:44.390
So what I say to you, God is all in.

21:44.450 --> 21:48.857
You go all in.

21:51.200 --> 22:10.290
Breathe in and breathe out and receive the everyday gift that God seeks to give you and then allow yourself to come alive.

22:11.650 --> 22:17.663
and be the gift that the world needs you to be.

22:20.108 --> 22:21.992
Okay, everybody hold your fingers like this.

22:23.234 --> 22:23.755
No, I'm not.

22:26.401 --> 22:26.962
Let us pray.

